6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to counties and county officers;
directing county offices and courts to offer option
8 to pay via credit card for all transactions;
permitting county offices and courts to pass on
9 service fee; directing county offices and courts to
provide forms; prohibiting charging a fee for forms;
10 mandating county offices and courts have a notary
during business hours; permitting one notary for
11 county offices within a single building; prohibiting
notaries from charging a fee; providing for
12 codification; and providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 272 of Title 19, unless there is
18 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 All county offices and courts shall offer the option to pay via
20 credit card for all transactions. County offices and courts shall
21 be allowed to pass the service fee onto the person requesting to pay
22 via credit card.
