1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 273 of Title 19, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 All county offices, including courts, shall be responsible for
5 providing any forms necessary to citizens of the county when
6 conducting business or legal proceedings with that county office or
7 court. County offices and courts may not charge a fee for providing
8 or printing such forms.
9 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
10 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 274 of Title 19, unless there is
11 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
12 A. Every county office, including the county clerk's office,
13 the county treasurer's office, the county assessor's office, and the
14 county courthouse, shall have a notary available during business
15 hours.
16 B. The notary may not charge a fee for their services.
17 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
